                  </hi>. I am a labourer, and live at Abingdon, in Carabridge<lb></lb>shire. I came up to mow, and was employed by Mr. Higginas. On the 23rd of June I laid my waistcoat in the field, about ten yards from the hay—I lost my waistcoat, my bag, and all the other things stated—these are them—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them</hi>)—I had seen them all safe about eight o'clock that morning.</p>
